14
00:00:56.850 --> 00:01:00.187
3.0 What Is Maintaining Position

15
00:01:00.187 --> 00:01:12.750
3.0.1 Maintaining position means that after reaching W_p, your most important 30 non-kin social relationships/friends (hereafter F30) maintain stable positive expectations of you

16
00:01:12.750 --> 00:01:17.075
a，This of course requires emotional commitment and long-term effort.

17
00:01:17.075 --> 00:01:22.887
Generally, there are two primary task lines: financial security and maintaining dignity

18
00:01:22.887 --> 00:01:29.437
b，A person can generally only sustain direct emotional connections with ~150 people (Dunbar's number).

19
00:01:29.437 --> 00:01:34.950
F30 represents the 20% accounting for 80% of importance among them.

20
00:01:34.950 --> 00:01:44.137
3.0.2 The method of maintaining position refers to the techniques for achieving both financial security and maintaining dignity — neither is dispensable.

21
00:01:44.137 --> 00:01:48.237
This chapter is divided into 3H1 and 3H2

22
00:01:48.237 --> 00:01:55.300
3.0.2.1 Financial security means ensuring that principal is never subject to permanent loss

23
00:01:55.300 --> 00:02:00.512
a，Concretely: in every medium-term period, net worth must not fall below e的负一次方

24
00:02:00.512 --> 00:02:08.712
b，In theory, wealth management methods can recover assets by e× over 7 years, so it suffices to stably keep assets above e的负一次方

25
00:02:08.712 --> 00:02:16.062
3.0.2.2 Maintaining dignity means ensuring that F30 will support you in the next important win-win move

26
00:02:16.062 --> 00:02:22.387
a，As the Chairman said, "Politics means making as many friends as possible and as few enemies as possible

27
00:02:22.387 --> 00:02:28.762
Historically, the Chairman placed extraordinary importance on comrades who supported him during adversity.

28
00:02:28.762 --> 00:02:38.350
b，At the margin, this means that within some social domain, "becoming someone's new friend" is a self-reinforcing conformist behavior rather than anti-conformist behavior.

29
00:02:38.350 --> 00:02:46.212
Further, within any social domain, having a base group that operates on a goodwill assumption toward you is the foundation for making new friends

30
00:02:46.212 --> 00:02:54.962
If no such group happens to exist, making new friends requires switching to a different social domain — colloquially called "restarting one's reputation

31
00:02:54.962 --> 00:02:58.087
3H1. Financial Security

32
00:02:58.087 --> 00:03:07.662
We will demonstrate that perpetual financial freedom is an endogenous equilibrium state of resource self-sufficiency, hereafter called "endogenous financial security

33
00:03:07.662 --> 00:03:16.375
The financial state and maintenance work at W_p but before reaching W_H is hereafter called "exogenous financial security

34
00:03:16.375 --> 00:03:21.775
3.1 Perpetual Financial Freedom / Endogenous Financial Security

35
00:03:21.775 --> 00:03:27.100
3.1.0 Mathematical Model of Endogenous Financial Security

36
00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:34.437
Assume M_i has initial wealth W_i1, where W_i1 大于等于 W_H

37
00:03:34.437 --> 00:03:57.787
3.1.0.1 Let M_i's annual total resource consumption (e.g., living expenses, inflation, business risks) be factorized as discount consumption factor R_iD, R_iD ∈ (0, e−1], D for discount; risk-free return rate R_iF, R_iF ∈ (−100%, R_m), F for risk-free

38
00:03:57.787 --> 00:04:01.412
a，Factorizing R_iD is reasonable.

39
00:04:01.412 --> 00:04:08.287
The resources consumed to maintain the status quo are not fixed but scale with current wealth W_i1

40
00:04:08.287 --> 00:04:16.700
R_iD = e−1 means consuming down to e的负一次方 per year; larger R_iD values have no meaningful discussion value

41
00:04:16.700 --> 00:04:22.425
b，Risk-free return R_iF is an independent variable with its own significance.

42
00:04:22.425 --> 00:04:28.200
If M_i takes on business risks, R_iD increases correspondingly

43
00:04:28.200 --> 00:04:34.612
R_iF can certainly be negative; −100% means losing everything within a year

44
00:04:34.612 --> 00:04:41.650
R_iF does not exceed R_m; no asset's long-term compound return can exceed R_m

45
00:04:41.812 --> 00:04:46.187
3.1.0.2 The subscript i is necessary.

46
00:04:46.137 --> 00:04:54.937
For different M_i, R_iD/R_iF values differ entirely, even if their W_i1 is identical.

47
00:04:54.937 --> 00:05:01.612
Each M_i differs enormously in risk appetite, lifestyle habits, ability, and family culture.

48
00:05:01.612 --> 00:05:12.099
3.1.0.3 In year two, W_i2 = W_i1(1+R_iF)/(1+R_iD).

49
00:05:12.099 --> 00:05:21.337
Generally, W_i,n+1 = W_i1[(1+R_iF)/(1+R_iD)]ⁿ ...

50
00:05:21.508 --> 00:05:25.583
3.1.0.4 If R_iF  b.

51
00:05:25.533 --> 00:05:42.695
In (), let W_i1 = W_H, n=60, R_iD=4%, R_iF=2%, then W_55 = e的负一次方 W_H, 3×18 = 54 years to fall below W_H;

52
00:05:42.695 --> 00:05:50.595
This is a typical indicator set explaining "why do rationally pragmatic yet non-resilient families lose wealth across three generations?

53
00:05:50.595 --> 00:05:56.645
It can be viewed as the gentlest form of W_H degradation — the Degradation Method

54
00:05:56.645 --> 00:06:04.758
3.1.0.5 Perpetual financial freedom thus requires R_iF 大于等于 R_iD, and this is achievable

55
00:06:04.758 --> 00:06:12.258
3.1.1 The first principle of endogenous financial security is maintaining R_iF 大于等于 R_iD

56
00:06:12.258 --> 00:06:17.270
a，Why does R_iF 大于等于 R_iD not violate entropy increase?

57
00:06:17.270 --> 00:06:20.483
Because it has real commercial significance.

58
00:06:20.483 --> 00:06:26.545
b，That is, once W_H is reached, its risk-free growth rate can resist attrition.

59
00:06:26.545 --> 00:06:33.308
3.1.1.1 It is well known that growth comes from innovation/new things/new concepts developing.

60
00:06:33.308 --> 00:06:44.358
3.1.1.2 For any new thing, establishing and achieving widespread acceptance of its value in era T generally requires endorsement from influential M during era T−1

61
00:06:44.358 --> 00:06:49.583
Colloquially "setting up the table," "building the canopy," "the people back the winner

62
00:06:49.583 --> 00:06:56.008
Value-system reshaping that does NOT require T−1 era M endorsement is called "value revolution.

63
00:06:56.008 --> 00:06:58.695
Value revolutions are rare.

64
00:06:58.695 --> 00:07:05.258
a，NFTs being widely recognized as investable required Steph Curry using an NFT ape avatar.

65
00:07:05.258 --> 00:07:14.945
b，BTC being widely recognized as investable required large traditional financial institutions and even national central banks including it in asset allocations.

66
00:07:14.945 --> 00:07:20.183
c，NFTs/BTC then appreciated dramatically during this process.

67
00:07:20.183 --> 00:07:23.420
What did Curry or central banks need to do?

68
00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:25.433
d，Nothing at all.

69
00:07:25.433 --> 00:07:28.095
Their returns were zero-risk.

70
00:07:28.095 --> 00:07:32.245
Their contribution to "setting up the table" was indispensable.

71
00:07:32.245 --> 00:07:41.883
3.1.1.3 M's existence/participation/endorsement itself carries indispensable milestone value in a new thing/concept's development.

72
00:07:41.883 --> 00:07:48.295
Conversely, every new class of assets inevitably produces its own representative new M (or several).

73
00:07:48.295 --> 00:07:52.845
Colloquially "seated at the table," "has a say," "the birth of a faction

74
00:07:52.845 --> 00:07:58.220
a，The essential difference in becoming an M is that other Ms consider you one of their own

75
00:07:58.220 --> 00:08:03.408
b，As long as your money came from legitimate sources, everyone assumes you're capable.

76
00:08:03.408 --> 00:08:09.845
As long as you don't sabotage yourself, everyone factors you in as "always being there" when thinking about things

77
00:08:09.845 --> 00:08:17.495
c，Concretely, they'll consult you on matters, reach out when opportunities arise, and if they must harm you they'll give you advance notice.

78
00:08:17.495 --> 00:08:23.395
3.1.2 The threshold for M status in the 2020s is W_H

79
00:08:23.395 --> 00:08:34.970
3.1.2.1 It is generally accepted that reaching W_H represents an extraordinary commercial achievement comparable to world-class achievements in other fields without being overshadowed.

80
00:08:34.970 --> 00:08:39.008
I want to become an athlete who earns W_H.

81
00:08:39.008 --> 00:08:40.983
LeBron James

82
00:08:40.983 --> 00:08:49.358
3.1.2.2 Money is the image of reason and storyline condensed upon you; it is an endogenous variable of reason and storyline.

83
00:08:49.358 --> 00:08:58.083
3.1.2.3 If you/your family's existence has enduring value, perpetual financial freedom is not an objective but a byproduct.

84
00:08:58.083 --> 00:09:04.320
3.1.3 The logical chain above is "if and only if" — meaning its converse theorems also hold

85
00:09:04.320 --> 00:09:12.633
3.1.3.1 Converse theorem I: Below W_H, accessible investment opportunities are not risk-free cake

86
00:09:12.633 --> 00:09:18.458
a，Colloquially "not seated at the table" — people assume you'll probably lose it all through incompetence.

87
00:09:18.458 --> 00:09:22.045
b，This is the academic definition of old money.

88
00:09:22.045 --> 00:09:26.458
Below this threshold, family legacy cannot genuinely exist.

89
00:09:26.458 --> 00:09:30.695
3.1.3.2 "How others treat you is priceless.

90
00:09:30.695 --> 00:09:41.845
If you happen to not be at W_H, what truly belongs to you is only memories and experiences from every amusement park visited, and the genuine feelings given and received along the way

91
00:09:41.845 --> 00:09:52.158
3.1.3.3 Converse theorem II: If you or your family's existence lacks enduring value, then W_in > W_H cannot persist long-term

92
00:09:52.158 --> 00:09:59.795
a，W_H is merely a symbolic expression that you remain at the table, while the table itself is perpetually renewed.

93
00:09:59.795 --> 00:10:05.008
b，Mechanical caution/frugality/risk avoidance has limited effect.

94
00:10:05.008 --> 00:10:10.258
You cannot preserve through mere protection alone — W_H must carry weight

95
00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:17.495
If Li Shishi in Water Margin is historically the same person, then Emperor Daojun was Emperor Huizong of Song.

96
00:10:17.445 --> 00:10:24.195
That is, within single-digit years after Song Jiang's execution, Huizong was captured by the Jin dynasty.

97
00:10:24.195 --> 00:10:28.995
3.1.4 How to achieve R_iF 大于等于 R_iD?

98
00:10:28.995 --> 00:10:36.632
3.1.4.0 After reaching W_H, simply "fulfill duties without self-sabotage" suffices

99
00:10:36.796 --> 00:10:50.896
3.1.4.1 "Fulfilling duties without self-sabotage" means being widely perceived as having made maximum effort to preserve one's own value (commercial/social/influence), without slackening, rather than allowing it to casually dissipate

100
00:10:50.846 --> 00:10:52.958
This is a high bar.

101
00:10:52.958 --> 00:11:00.183
Some W_H families even codify this requirement in a written document, colloquially "family precepts.

102
00:11:00.183 --> 00:11:07.621
3.1.4.2 Not self-sabotaging guarantees R_iF > 0; otherwise it becomes a massive negative

103
00:11:07.621 --> 00:11:12.146
Not self-sabotaging means progress — it's only a question of speed.

104
00:11:12.146 --> 00:11:17.533
3.1.4.3 Fulfilling duties makes F30 think you're still capable.

105
00:11:17.533 --> 00:11:23.858
Across successive win-win moves, R_iF automatically rises above R_iD

106
00:11:23.858 --> 00:11:25.983
==a.

107
00:11:25.983 --> 00:11:30.583
In practice, R_iD median roughly equals 4%.

108
00:11:30.583 --> 00:11:37.433
Doing nothing (R_iF=0), 25 years to consume down to e的负一次方 or confirmed degradation

109
00:11:37.433 --> 00:11:46.933
a，Without self-sabotage, beating R_iD is not difficult — colloquially "you may not be fierce yourself, but you always have that one classmate who's pretty fierce

110
00:11:46.933 --> 00:11:51.096
Boss Jia and Teacher Y both lost their original businesses.

111
00:11:51.096 --> 00:11:57.646
But Teacher Y didn't self-sabotage, so his seat remained — he's still seen as a faction head, still in the game.

112
00:11:57.646 --> 00:12:03.871
3.1.5 How does contemporary financial freedom evolve into perpetual financial freedom?

113
00:12:03.871 --> 00:12:10.271
3.1.5.1 Concretely, how to achieve W_p 到 W_H?

114
00:12:10.271 --> 00:12:15.358
3.1.5.2 This process cannot be completed by the non-elite

115
00:12:15.358 --> 00:12:21.833
W_H has reached a magnitude where steady-state existence is impossible without carrying weight.

116
00:12:21.833 --> 00:12:28.258
3.1.5.3 How the elite complete this process — see Chapter 4: How to Make Things Happen

117
00:12:28.258 --> 00:12:32.446
3.1.6 W_H in Practice

118
00:12:32.446 --> 00:12:40.896
3.1.6.1 The foregoing merely established numerically that W_H has the opportunity for perpetual existence.

119
00:12:40.896 --> 00:12:47.933
In practice, the most common forms of W_H are industrial operations and industrial investment.

120
00:12:47.933 --> 00:12:51.821
You must carry weight, serve original dishes to the world.

121
00:12:51.821 --> 00:12:54.733
Buffett isn't just about stock picking.

122
00:12:54.733 --> 00:13:01.608
The combined annual revenue of companies he controls/operators reaches the hundreds of billions USD scale.

123
00:13:01.608 --> 00:13:09.458
3.1.6.2 W_H that carries weight thoroughly enjoys earning money, like repeatedly playing a game they excel at.

124
00:13:09.458 --> 00:13:16.846
a，Since they typically excel at only one type of game, investments are extremely concentrated, not diversified at all.

125
00:13:16.846 --> 00:13:24.296
b，Beyond what's allocated to the family office, everything else defaults to industrial operations and industrial investment.

126
00:13:24.296 --> 00:13:31.808
c，This naturally includes aggressive distressed asset acquisition — see Chapter 2 Appendix: Reversal Investing ZD Group

127
00:13:31.808 --> 00:13:36.646
3.1.7 Two Examples of W_H Forms

128
00:13:36.646 --> 00:13:43.183
3.1.7.1 Semiconductor CEO A, net worth at tens of billions USD scale

129
00:13:43.183 --> 00:13:48.246
a，Aside from donations, nearly all his personal capital goes to one thing:

130
00:13:48.246 --> 00:13:55.771
b，Acquiring valuable small companies in semiconductors worldwide that he can buy (e.g., Japan, South Korea, Israel).

131
00:13:55.771 --> 00:14:04.071
c，Because he knows best + he's relatively richest + he puts capital to greatest use, win rate is extremely high and he enjoys it daily.

132
00:14:04.071 --> 00:14:10.808
3.1.7.2 New energy vehicle CEO B, net worth at tens of billions HKD scale

133
00:14:10.808 --> 00:14:20.258
a，Beyond living-expense money left for the family office, the vast majority of his funds went entirely into three or four new industries representing humanity's future.

134
00:14:20.258 --> 00:14:23.733
b，My child's previous idol was Howard Hughes.

135
00:14:23.733 --> 00:14:28.196
Since meeting him, my child says he's China's version of Howard Hughes

136
00:14:28.196 --> 00:14:31.746
3.2 Exogenous Financial Security

137
00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:36.821
3.2.0 First Principle of Exogenous Financial Security

138
00:14:36.821 --> 00:14:46.971
3.2.0.1 If you are an elite W_p, the first principle of exogenous financial security is continuing to serve original dishes to the world.

139
00:14:46.971 --> 00:14:53.046
Your original contributions as the driver of sustained wealth growth, not your money's contributions.

140
00:14:53.046 --> 00:14:57.021
At the W_p level, money is ordinary.

141
00:14:57.021 --> 00:15:07.208
3.2.0.2 If you are a non-elite W_p, the first principle of exogenous financial security is heavy reliance on accessible club investments.

142
00:15:07.208 --> 00:15:13.208
Hereafter in this chapter, W_p defaults to non-elite W_p.

143
00:15:13.208 --> 00:15:25.696
3.2.0.3 Club investment refers to projects operated by M, with widespread F30 participation, denoted C_l, with participants denoted c_l, CL for Club

144
00:15:25.696 --> 00:15:30.346
3.2.1 How Does W_p Allocate Assets?

145
00:15:30.508 --> 00:15:37.233
A typical Chinese family office's approximate allocation across asset categories (with standard variance

146
00:15:37.183 --> 00:15:41.820
3.2.1.1 e的负一次方 / 37% floor assets

147
00:15:41.820 --> 00:15:44.570
a，22% real estate

148
00:15:44.570 --> 00:15:49.508
Occasionally also allocating to physical assets (oil & gas/gold)

149
00:15:49.508 --> 00:15:52.608
Chinese people prefer real estate more.

150
00:15:52.608 --> 00:15:57.070
b，15% cash/cash equivalents/fixed income

151
00:15:57.220 --> 00:16:01.770
Must always maintain capacity for club investment participation.

152
00:16:01.720 --> 00:16:07.932
In fact, due to the existence of club investments, cash is actually the most aggressive asset.

153
00:16:07.932 --> 00:16:17.557
Due to agency problems with family office managers and the pitfall nature of structured fixed-income products, the only safe fixed-income product is short-term U.S. Treasuries.

154
00:16:17.557 --> 00:16:23.557
3.2.1.2 e的负一次方 / 37% alternative assets (offensive assets)

155
00:16:23.557 --> 00:16:26.632
32% alternative assets

156
00:16:26.632 --> 00:16:30.982
PE/VC funds and attached co-investment allocations

157
00:16:30.982 --> 00:16:35.445
Becoming a fund investor in multiple PE/VC firms.

158
00:16:35.445 --> 00:16:41.807
Beyond collecting financial returns, this can be viewed as joining an intellectually resource-leading club.

159
00:16:41.807 --> 00:16:49.607
This is one of the best ways to maintain broad contact with global cutting-edge advancement, second only to reading research papers oneself.

160
00:16:49.607 --> 00:16:57.220
SQ Fund consistently provides BD secondary-share discount allocations to its investors while locking in its own returns.

161
00:16:57.220 --> 00:17:01.095
Hedge funds/quantitative funds/BTC

162
00:17:01.095 --> 00:17:04.782
5% art/annual donation commitments

163
00:17:04.782 --> 00:17:09.795
Building two resumes: one for art disposition and one for charitable giving.

164
00:17:09.795 --> 00:17:15.570
3.2.1.3 (1 − 2e的负一次方) / 26% standard assets

165
00:17:15.570 --> 00:17:23.170
a. U.S. equities: MAG7/pharma/Nasdaq; A-shares/HK equities: Kweichow Moutai/Tencent

166
00:17:23.170 --> 00:17:26.295
3.2.2 Club Investment

167
00:17:26.295 --> 00:17:36.757
3.2.2.0 Non-elite W_p cannot engage in industrial/industrial investment (or prior industry has failed and transformation is impossible).

168
00:17:36.757 --> 00:17:43.670
3.2.2.1 Maintaining dignity sustains one's social circle and updates market consensus value.

169
00:17:43.670 --> 00:17:51.195
3.2.2.2 One then learns of recent C_l opportunities (though not necessarily proactively invited)

170
00:17:51.195 --> 00:17:58.620
a，Group A privatization and delisting, Group B new-track subsidiary spin-off, Giant C pre-IPO final funding round.

171
00:17:58.620 --> 00:18:04.107
3.2.2.3 C_l is (a priori) zero-risk for M.

172
00:18:04.107 --> 00:18:15.470
3.2.2.4 However, due to differences in trading position and information timeliness, C_l is not 100% positively returning for all c_l participants.

173
00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:27.345
a，Empirically its return distribution approximates 50% at 2x, 20% at 1x, 30% at 0x, yielding ~90% probability of profit after three compound rounds

174
00:18:27.345 --> 00:18:32.332
3.2.3 Participate in C_l once every few years.

175
00:18:32.332 --> 00:18:36.620
With luck, exogenous financial security can be maintained

176
00:18:36.620 --> 00:18:43.995
3.2.3.1 Why can't wealth management methods recover R_m after reaching W_p?

177
00:18:43.995 --> 00:18:48.220
a，Wealth management methods involve highly concentrated holdings.

178
00:18:48.220 --> 00:18:56.120
At W_p, there is too much hard-won capital to bear such idiosyncratic risk; black swans must be guarded against.

179
00:18:56.120 --> 00:19:01.595
Even Tencent dares not go all-in anymore — diversification starts to make sense.

180
00:19:01.595 --> 00:19:07.345
b，Wealth management methods require ultra-long-term judgment certainty regarding The Portfolio.

181
00:19:07.345 --> 00:19:10.532
No target maintains certainty forever.

182
00:19:10.532 --> 00:19:16.595
c，In practice, W_p struggles to concentrate assets in just 2–5 targets

183
00:19:16.595 --> 00:19:28.220
3.2.3.2 Per 3.2.1.1, you can only deploy a very small proportion of total assets into C_l investments, aiming to lift overall portfolio R_iF.

184
00:19:28.220 --> 00:19:31.970
a，This demands high returns from C_l.

185
00:19:31.970 --> 00:19:37.432
Meanwhile, C_l carries risk — three consecutive wrong bets cannot occur.

186
00:19:37.432 --> 00:19:44.520
b，But non-elite W_p must accept this risk; occasional extraordinary returns make it worthwhile

187
00:19:44.520 --> 00:19:55.632
c，C_l and X_l share the same source, but X_l offers better pricing and higher returns because it monetizes one's own influence rather than mere dependent participation

188
00:19:55.632 --> 00:19:59.670
3.2.4 Two Examples of Club Investment

189
00:19:59.670 --> 00:20:04.157
3.2.4.1 Mr. LJC's family investment

190
00:20:04.157 --> 00:20:09.257
a，Mr. LJC served as China's wealthiest individual for a long time.

191
00:20:09.257 --> 00:20:14.882
After a series of ordinary family investments, he invested in Zoom during the pandemic.

192
00:20:14.882 --> 00:20:21.382
By April 2025, Zoom holdings accounted for as much as 1/3 of Mr. L's total assets.

193
00:20:21.382 --> 00:20:26.832
3.2.4.2 An internet company's capability-chain spin-off IPO

194
00:20:26.832 --> 00:20:35.332
a，After going public, this internet group spun off each operational link of its core business into separate IPOs, all under the original brand.

195
00:20:35.332 --> 00:20:42.882
b，By April 2025, five publicly listed companies sharing the brand had been established, with a sixth imminent.

196
00:20:42.882 --> 00:20:47.395
Each would have been profitable if invested in from spin-off through IPO.

197
00:20:47.548 --> 00:20:55.310
c，If you happen to be in the founder's social circle of this internet group, you could effortlessly maintain position through these opportunities.

198
00:20:55.260 --> 00:21:02.235
3.2.5 It should be noted that "club project" is a logical concept whose form need not even be investment

199
00:21:02.235 --> 00:21:09.598
a，Club projects refer to win-win moves generated by F30 participating in designated projects initiated by M

200
00:21:09.748 --> 00:21:18.985
This is a litmus test for M: projects they initiate will definitely proceed (generally within 18 months) regardless of F30 participation levels.

201
00:21:18.935 --> 00:21:27.823
Whereas W_p cannot initiate/pursue projects opposed by their entire F30, and day-to-day activities lack predetermined certainty.

202
00:21:27.823 --> 00:21:37.123
b，Any project whose expected return exceeds market rates qualifies as a club project, colloquially "dependent participation"/"licking the pot rim.

203
00:21:37.123 --> 00:21:44.285
Non-investment "club projects" (e.g., participating in recruitment or appearing in new productions) are omitted here.

204
00:21:44.285 --> 00:21:52.835
3.2.6 Before W_p, long-term financial security does not exist, hence position maintenance is unnecessary

205
00:21:52.835 --> 00:22:01.435
3.2.6.1 Before W_p / wealth management success, R_iD greatly exceeds R_iF

206
00:22:01.435 --> 00:22:04.698
a，Note that R_iD is a factor.

207
00:22:04.698 --> 00:22:11.348
When asset scale is small, fixed living expenses produce an R_iD far exceeding 4%.

208
00:22:11.348 --> 00:22:19.798
b，On the other hand, before reaching W_p, low probability of accessing club investments means R_iF approaches zero.

209
00:22:19.798 --> 00:22:28.073
Note that wage income and investment income are both not risk-free; increasing risk-return inevitably synchronously increases R_iD.

210
00:22:28.073 --> 00:22:33.948
c，The above analysis targets expectation; in reality, variance plays a larger role.

211
00:22:33.948 --> 00:22:36.748
One blowout event ends the game.

212
00:22:36.748 --> 00:22:42.585
Those between W_F and W_p are hereafter called the middle class.

213
00:22:42.585 --> 00:22:50.023
The middle class cannot withstand one serious illness, unemployment, divorce, investment failure, or other life accident...

214
00:22:50.023 --> 00:22:54.673
Cannot withstand means permanent loss of principal, falling below e的负一次方.

215
00:22:54.673 --> 00:22:59.523
Over ultra-long horizons, these negative events inevitably arrive.

216
00:22:59.523 --> 00:23:06.098
Thus the middle class is not a state variable with stable meaning but a temporary probabilistic manifestation.

217
00:23:06.098 --> 00:23:12.985
3.2.6.2 In summary, the middle class possesses no meaningful concept of financial security.

218
00:23:12.985 --> 00:23:23.885
3.2.6.3 The rational approach is applying wealth management and shore-reaching methods, bearing necessary (concentrated investment) risks, and reaching shore as early as possible

219
00:23:23.885 --> 00:23:26.998
3H2. Maintaining Dignity

220
00:23:26.998 --> 00:23:35.310
3.3 Maintaining dignity means doing everything possible to prevent F30 from forming negative suspicions or unnecessary conjectures

221
00:23:35.310 --> 00:23:44.523
3.3.1 The first principle of maintaining dignity is: never offend those truly beyond offending (collectively termed M alongside the aforementioned M)

222
00:23:44.523 --> 00:23:52.960
3.3.2 Those truly beyond offending are individuals whose unilateral opinion can alter F30's baseline goodwill assumption toward you

223
00:23:52.960 --> 00:23:56.673
3.4 Core Elements of Maintaining Dignity

224
00:23:56.673 --> 00:24:01.785
3.4.1 Core element I of maintaining dignity: Social vigilance

225
00:24:01.785 --> 00:24:05.573
3.4.1.1 M always exists.

226
00:24:05.573 --> 00:24:12.260
a，The wealthier one is, the greater the need for cautious real-time situational judgment of one's social environment.

227
00:24:12.260 --> 00:24:15.723
Colloquially "having situational awareness.

228
00:24:15.723 --> 00:24:19.373
b，Long-term probability of offending M is high.

229
00:24:19.373 --> 00:24:25.748
Relatively speaking, the probability of getting three consecutive club investment bets wrong is quite low.

230
00:24:25.748 --> 00:24:31.160
3.4.1.2 Lenin said, all things are universally interconnected.

231
00:24:31.160 --> 00:24:34.360
a，You don't know what M looks like when they appear.

232
00:24:34.360 --> 00:24:43.760
b，Actions you take to maintain relationship with M_i may offend M_j or even unknown M₊ (M that M needs to maintain for position preservation).

233
00:24:43.760 --> 00:24:48.973
c，You don't know which individuals connected to M (hereafter m) influence M.

234
00:24:48.973 --> 00:24:54.973
d，People's mindsets vary wildly; you don't know how certain moves might trigger thoughts in M/m.

235
00:24:54.973 --> 00:25:02.110
3.4.1.3 The direct corollary: unless necessary, avoid dealing with many M simultaneously

236
00:25:02.110 --> 00:25:07.273
In practice, many W_H interact with only one M per phase.

237
00:25:07.273 --> 00:25:10.860
Switching M is colloquially "changing allegiance.

238
00:25:10.860 --> 00:25:16.423
3.4.2 Core element II of maintaining dignity: Treat others generously

239
00:25:16.423 --> 00:25:22.035
3.4.2.1 This is virtue; doing the right thing is reason enough in itself.

240
00:25:22.035 --> 00:25:32.623
3.4.2.2 This is also a direct corollary of 3.4.1: treating people sincerely and generously makes it easier to earn understanding and support from M and m.

241
00:25:32.623 --> 00:25:38.673
3.4.3 Core element III of maintaining dignity: "When in Rome, do as Romans do

242
00:25:38.673 --> 00:25:48.798
3.4.3.0 "When in Rome, do as Romans do" refers to a social assimilation strategy of proactively integrating into F30's mainstream lifestyle patterns.

243
00:25:48.964 --> 00:25:55.964
3.4.3.1 This is obvious: non-conformity triggers unnecessary suspicions and conjectures.

244
00:25:55.914 --> 00:26:04.639
3.4.3.2 You must maintain emotional bonds with F30 anyway; being similar to them across dimensions saves effort over the long term.

245
00:26:04.639 --> 00:26:13.264
3.4.3.3 This explains why in the 2020s you need to build two resumes: one for art disposition and one for charitable giving.

246
00:26:13.420 --> 00:26:19.607
3.4.4 Core element IV of maintaining dignity: "Marital happiness"==

247
00:26:19.557 --> 00:26:24.970
3.4.4.1 This is a direct corollary of 3.4.3.

248
00:26:24.970 --> 00:26:29.432
Spouse = most important F30 member, hereafter "F1.

249
00:26:29.432 --> 00:26:35.782
3.4.4.2 F1 ideally shares your interests and stays within mutual expectations.

250
00:26:35.782 --> 00:26:40.345
This also falls within F29 expectations, saving effort.

251
00:26:40.345 --> 00:26:46.282
a，Success or failure of most short-to-medium-term goals changes your life by at most x%.

252
00:26:46.282 --> 00:26:52.920
Professional/industry choice is 10x%; city/work/promotion are all x%.

253
00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:56.345
b，Marriage represents a 50% change.

254
00:26:56.345 --> 00:27:03.082
In corporate finance terms, you issued 100% new equity and swapped it for F1's 100%.

255
00:27:03.082 --> 00:27:06.670
Your lives had no intersection in the first half.

256
00:27:06.670 --> 00:27:18.695
Suddenly your decade of study/natural brilliance/leadership acquired exchangeable value, swapable for F1's decade of study/bright intellect/distinguished lineage — precious beyond measure, cherish it.

257
00:27:18.695 --> 00:27:27.195
3.4.4.3 If this is not the case, revert to "treat others generously" — i.e., exercise high fault tolerance toward your F1.

258
00:27:27.195 --> 00:27:32.945
Buffett says long-term happy marriage needs only one ingredient: low expectations of F1.

259
00:27:32.945 --> 00:27:40.120
